The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Amazon plans call centre in Hyderabad

 New Delhi, June 8 (PTI): Leading online business house Amazon.com Inc today announced plans to open a customer service centre in Hyderabad. 

 Scheduled to be operational in the second half of 2005, this centre will offer additional email support to its customers.

 The centre, which will be the seventh customer service centre of Amazon.com, will provide 100 new jobs.

 As more and more of our customers come from outside the United States, it is important that we have customer service representatives available to respond to our customers, irrespective of the time zone they might be in. The additional resources provided by our new Hyderabad office will serve our customers more quickly and effectively, said the companys director of India (customer service operations), Pritam Baxi.

 A fortune 500 company, Amazon.com Inc offers through its online store a wide variety of new and used products catering to different segments such as beauty, health and personal care, jewellery, music, toys, home and garden. 




